data.enText: to try to sell goods by going from house to house or from place to place

data.chText: 他的工作是上门推销抹布和刷子。
data.enText: He worked as a door-to-door salesman peddling cloths and brushes.

data.chText: 兜售，宣传，传播（思想、消息）
data.enText: to spread an idea or story in order to get people to accept it

data.chText: 所有的政府发言人都在宣扬这个官方路线。
data.enText: This line (= publicly stated opinion) is being peddled by all the government spokesmen.

tr: sell or offer for sale from place to place

value.def: Someone who peddles things goes from place to place trying to sell them.

example.ex: His attempts to peddle his paintings around London's tiny gallery scene proved unsuccessful.
example.tran: 他到伦敦小画廊兜售自己的画作，结果碰了一鼻子灰。

value.def: Someone who peddles drugs sells illegal drugs.

example.ex: When a drug pusher offered the Los Angeles youngster $100 to peddle drugs, Jack refused.
example.tran: 一个毒贩给杰克100美元让他贩卖毒品时，这个洛杉矶少年拒绝了。

example.ex: The war against drug peddling is all about cash.
example.tran: 禁毒斗争归根到底是钱的问题。

value.def: If someone peddles an idea or a piece of information, they try very hard to get people to accept it.

example.ex: They even set up their own news agency to peddle anti-isolationist propaganda.
example.tran: 他们甚至设立了自己的通讯社来宣扬反孤立主义。
